{"name": "mpegdash", "metadata": {"name": "mpegdash", "version": "0.4.0", "classifiers": ["Environment :: Other Environment", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Python Modules"], "home_page": "https://github.com/sangwonl/python-mpegdash", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "MPEG-DASH MPD(Media Presentation Description) Parser", "upload_time": 1705447997}, "documentation": ["\n# python-mpegdash\n\nMPEG-DASH MPD (Media Presentation Description) Parser compatible with Python 3+.\n\n[![Build Status](https://img.shields.io/github/workflow/status/sangwonl/python-mpegdash/Build%20Status?label=Python%203%2B%20builds)](https://github.com/sangwonl/python-mpegdash/actions?query=workflow%3A%22Build+Status%22)\n[![License](https://img.shields.io/github/license/sangwonl/python-mpegdash?style=flat)](https://github.com/sangwonl/python-mpegdash/blob/master/LICENSE)\n\n* * *\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\n$ pip install mpegdash\n```\n\n* * *\n\n## Test\n\n```bash\n$ python -m unittest discover\n```\n\n* * *\n\n## Usage\n\n```py\nfrom mpegdash.parser import MPEGDASHParser\n\n# Parse from file path\nmpd_path = './tests/mpd-samples/sample-001.mpd'\nmpd = MPEGDASHParser.parse(mpd_path)\n\n# Parse from url\nmpd_url = 'http://yt-dash-mse-test.commondatastorage.googleapis.com/media/motion-20120802-manifest.mpd'\nmpd = MPEGDASHParser.parse(mpd_url)\n\n# Parse from string\nmpd_string = '''\n<MPD xmlns=\"urn:mpeg:DASH:schema:MPD:2011\" mediaPresentationDuration=\"PT0H1M52.43S\" minBufferTime=\"PT1.5S\"\nprofiles=\"urn:mpeg:dash:profile:isoff-on-demand:2011\" type=\"static\">\n  <Period duration=\"PT0H1M52.43S\" start=\"PT0S\">\n    <AdaptationSet>\n      <ContentComponent contentType=\"video\" id=\"1\" />\n      <Representation bandwidth=\"4190760\" codecs=\"avc1.640028\" height=\"1080\" id=\"1\" mimeType=\"video/mp4\" width=\"1920\">\n        <BaseURL>motion-20120802-89.mp4</BaseURL>\n        <SegmentBase indexRange=\"674-981\">\n          <Initialization range=\"0-673\" />\n        </SegmentBase>\n      </Representation>\n    </AdaptationSet>\n  </Period>\n</MPD>\n'''\nmpd = MPEGDASHParser.parse(mpd_string)\n\n# Write to xml file\nMPEGDASHParser.write(mpd, './tests/mpd-samples/output.mpd')\n```\n\n* * *\n\n## License\n\nThis project is released under the MIT license.\nPlease read and agree to the license before use, it can be found in the [LICENSE](LICENSE) file.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "mpegdash.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "mpegdash.utils._find_child_nodes_by_name", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "parent", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "name", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mpegdash.utils.parse_child_nodes", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "xmlnode", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "tag_name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "node_type", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mpegdash.utils.parse_node_value", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "xmlnode", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "value_type", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mpegdash.utils.parse_attr_value", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "xmlnode", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "attr_name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "value_type", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mpegdash.utils.write_child_node", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "xmlnode", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "tag_name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "node", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mpegdash.